article.headline: Youngstown St. 55, Detroit 48
article.story: YOUNGSTOWN, Ohio (AP) -- Byron Davis scored 13 points and John Barber scored 10 and had 10 rebounds as Youngstown State came from behind to beat Detroit, 55-48, Thursday night. Youngstown State (8-15, 4-9 Horizon League) trailed until midway through the second half when it scored eight straight to pull ahead 38-35, and the Penguins were never behind again. Detroit (5-17, 1-11) kept it close over the next several minutes. But then Barber made a free throw and a jumper, and Jack Liles grabbed Vance Cooksey's missed 3-pointer and slammed it home to put the Penguins ahead 52-44 with 2:21 left. The Titans didn't threaten again. Jon Goode led all scorers with 26 points, and Woody Paine added nine points for Detroit.
